l logics. The book will be relevant to Peirce scholars, mathematicians, and philosophers alike, thanks to thorough assessments of Peirce's mathematical heritage, compact surveys of the literature, and new perspectives offered through formal and modern mathematizations of the topics studied.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aLogic, Symbolic and mathematical. 0aMathematicsxPhilosophy. 4aExistenzgraph. 4aKontinuum. 4aMaxime. 4aNichtklassische Logik. 4aPeirce, Charles S. 4aPragmatismus. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Pragmatism.2bisacsh  aPeirce's continuum.  aexistential graphs.  anon-classical logics.  apragmatic maxim.1 aArengas, Gustavo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOostra, Arnold, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVargas, Francisco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZalamea, Fernando, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZalamea, Fernando, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022 Englishz978311099276208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022z9783110992755oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831107177160 cprintz978311071761740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311071763140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110717631423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110717631/original  a978-3-11-099276-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Engl